WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.840
The first major Tai Chi movement: we are positioned here, performing the notochordal wave.

2
00:00:06.220 --> 00:00:11.300
We return with the entire mesodermal movement.

3
00:00:11.980 --> 00:00:17.420
The notochordal wave, and beneath it, the complete mesodermal movement.

4
00:00:17.820 --> 00:00:19.620
Next, we focus on the brain.

5
00:00:21.900 --> 00:00:24.720
1. Cerebral growth.

6
00:00:24.940 --> 00:00:27.040
2. Cephalic flexion.

7
00:00:28.062 --> 00:00:32.162
3. Cervical flexion.

8
00:00:33.922 --> 00:00:37.062
4. Pontine flexion.

9
00:00:40.062 --> 00:00:42.062
5. Telencephalization.

10
00:00:49.202 --> 00:00:54.262
Renal movement. This constitutes an external rotation movement.

11
00:00:58.825 --> 00:01:05.465
Now, we will address the bladder and uterus, and

12
00:01:05.465 --> 00:01:06.005
then we return.

13
00:01:08.285 --> 00:01:10.025
Peritoneum, with the right hand positioned anteriorly.

14
00:01:11.225 --> 00:01:15.505
I grasp the ansa here, drawing it towards my hepatic side.

15
00:01:15.845 --> 00:01:18.725
The hand here descends and completes the rotation in this manner.

16
00:01:20.285 --> 00:01:22.845
In this manner, the ansa is positioned here before me.

17
00:01:22.845 --> 00:01:24.065
It expands.

18
00:01:25.528 --> 00:01:30.568
I pull this hand, locate the ansa here, and draw it towards my liver.

19
00:01:30.568 --> 00:01:31.068
Subsequently, this hand descends, ascends, and the other descends to form the terminal phase.

20
00:01:32.048 --> 00:01:37.168
Et  puis  la  main  ici  descend,  monte,  et  celle -là  descend  pour  former  la

21
00:01:37.168 --> 00:01:37.928
phase  terminale.

